1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:04,362
JavaScript classes also support static methods and fields

2
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:08,875
which are defined on the class itself rather than any objects created by it

3
00:00:09,238 --> 00:00:17,075
These are useful for defining utility functions or properties that are relevant to the class but don't depend on any specific instance

4
00:00:17,462 --> 00:00:22,025
Static methods and properties can be accessed without instantiating the class

5
00:00:22,425 --> 00:00:28,038
making them ideal for encapsulating code related to the class but not its individual instances

